               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_f1e1a79383b0a245b83da9d90d2fc3fc">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>There is also a prayer, a reply to a challenge to duel, the roll of Captain Whiting's Company in 1776, brief accounts, and a sketch of a camp. The book also contains four rhymed poems, one a pastoral, and three addressed to "Kate, the captains's lady".</p>
